Pasiap’s humble nature caused him to remain with his disciples after the other Immaculate Dragons left Creation behind.
It was the hands of Daana’d that shut the gates of the Underworld, forcing the Anathema’s souls to remain forever in the dark as punishment for their evil.
Certain texts of Daana’d suggest seeing beings that wield Essence as self-contained eddies in Creation.
Of all the Immaculate Dragons, none was as implacable a foe to the undead as Sextes Jylis.